summary:
15. Requests States to report on actions taken to implement measures within 90 days;

16. Urges cooperation with the Committee.
The Security Council:
- Urges all States to cooperate with the Committee, particularly by providing information on possible violations of measures imposed by paragraphs 7, 9, and 11;
- Determines to consider further steps for effective monitoring and implementation of these measures, including establishing a panel of experts;
- Requests the Secretary-General to report by 15 March 2005 on progress towards goals outlined in paragraph 13;
- Decides that measures imposed by paragraphs 9 and 11 shall enter into force on 15 December 2004, unless the Council determines before then that signatories have implemented their commitments under the Accra III Agreement and are moving towards full implementation of the Linas-Marcoussis Agreement;
- Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
